10000002.description: Daughter of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Dignified and elegant, as well as wise and strong.
10000002.name: Kamisato Ayaka

10000003.description: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.
10000003.name: Jean

10000005.description: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.
10000005.name: Aether

10000006.description: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Academia to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.
10000006.name: Lisa

10000007.description: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.
10000007.name: Lumine

10000014.description: Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.
10000014.name: Barbara

10000015.description: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.
10000015.name: Kaeya

10000016.description: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.
10000016.name: Diluc

10000020.description: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.
10000020.name: Razor

10000021.description: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.
10000021.name: Amber

10000022.description: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.
10000022.name: Venti

10000023.description: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.
10000023.name: Xiangling

10000024.description: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.
10000024.name: Beidou

10000025.description: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.
10000025.name: Xingqiu

10000026.description: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."
10000026.name: Xiao

10000027.description: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.
10000027.name: Ningguang

10000029.description: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius's confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.
10000029.name: Klee

10000030.description: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.
10000030.name: Zhongli

10000031.description: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.
10000031.name: Fischl

10000032.description: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.
10000032.name: Bennett

10000033.description: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.
10000033.name: Tartaglia

10000034.description: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.
10000034.name: Noelle

10000035.description: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.
10000035.name: Qiqi

10000036.description: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.
10000036.name: Chongyun

10000037.description: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.
10000037.name: Ganyu

10000038.description: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.
10000038.name: Albedo

10000039.description: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.
10000039.name: Diona

10000041.description: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.
10000041.name: Mona

10000042.description: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis's unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.
10000042.name: Keqing

10000043.description: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.
10000043.name: Sucrose

10000044.description: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.
10000044.name: Xinyan

10000045.description: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.
10000045.name: Rosaria

10000046.description: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.
10000046.name: Hu Tao

10000047.description: A wandering samurai from Inazuma who is currently with Liyue's Crux Fleet. A gentle and carefree soul whose heart hides a great many burdens from the past.
10000047.name: Kaedehara Kazuha

10000048.description: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.
10000048.name: Yanfei

10000049.description: Owner of Naganohara Fireworks. Known as "Queen of the Summer Festival," she excels in her craft of creating fireworks that symbolize people's hopes and dreams.
10000049.name: Yoimiya

10000050.description: The Kamisato Clan's housekeeper. A well-known "fixer" in Inazuma.
10000050.name: Thoma

10000051.description: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.
10000051.name: Eula

10000052.description: Her Excellency, the Almighty Narukami Ogosho, who promised the people of Inazuma an unchanging Eternity.
10000052.name: Raiden Shogun

10000053.description: A pint-sized ninja attached to the Shuumatsuban, who always seems sleep-deprived.
10000053.name: Sayu

10000054.description: The Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island. All of the island's affairs are at this young lady's fingertips.
10000054.name: Sangonomiya Kokomi

10000056.description: A general of the Tenryou Commission. Bold, decisive, and skilled in battle.
10000056.name: Kujou Sara

10000062.description: Formerly an outcast, now a hunter of unparalleled skill. Ready to do the right thing at any time.
10000062.name: Aloy
